cunstrucor overloading: it allows the class tohave multiple cunstuctoreach with the same name but with diff. parameter. this enables the object of the classto be inisialized in
various ways, provides flexibility in the program. when an object is created, compiler determines which cunstructor to call based on the argument provided during the object 
instantiation. the compiler looks for a constructor  whoose parameter listlike number of argument, type of argument and their order matches the argument passes during the object
creatation.



